Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "marti" in different forms and positions with English translations in parenthesis:

1. *Marti* je prvi mesec u proleću. (*March* is the first month of spring.)
2. Ove godine će *mart* biti kišovit. (This year *March* will be rainy.)
3. On voli da se šali tokom *marta*. (He likes to joke around during *March*.)
4. U *martu* često pada sneg u planinama. (In *March*, it often snows in the mountains.)
5. Danas sam kupio novi *martovski* kalendar. (Today I bought a new *March* calendar.)
6. *Martovska* revolucija je označila početak narodne borbe za oslobođenje od Turaka. (*The March* revolution marked the beginning of the people's struggle for liberation from the Turks.)
7. *Martovski* festival knjige će se održati sledećeg vikenda. (*March* book festival will be held next weekend.)
8. Često idem u *marti* na planinarenje. (I often go hiking in the *March*.)
9. *Martovski* dani su najbolje vreme za sadnju povrća. (*March* days are the best time for planting vegetables.)
10. *Marti* su u Srbiji poznati po slavi Svetog Josipa. (*March* is known in Serbia for the feast of Saint Joseph.)